# Supabase Configuration
# Get these values from your Supabase project dashboard: https://app.supabase.com

# Your Supabase project URL
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co

# Your Supabase anon/public key (safe to expose in frontend)
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key-here

# Instructions for setup:
# 1. Copy this file to .env.local (or .env)
# 2. Replace the values above with your actual Supabase credentials
# 3. For the reset-password.html page, add this script before loading reset-password.js:
#    <script>
#      window.SUPABASE_URL = 'your-actual-supabase-url';
#      window.SUPABASE_ANON_KEY = 'your-actual-anon-key';
#    </script>
#
# Note: Since this is a static site, you'll need to inject these values at build time
# or use a server-side configuration to serve them securely.

# Password Reset Flow Setup in Supabase:
# 1. Go to Authentication > URL Configuration in your Supabase dashboard
# 2. Set the "Redirect URL" for password reset to: https://yourdomain.com/reset-password.html
# 3. Enable the password reset flow in Authentication > Settings
# 4. Configure your email templates in Authentication > Email Templates